Title: ['JOAN']
Upvote: Been following this stock since its IPO. Started out at $12 a share and has dipped down to be consistent at $10-$11 a share low trading volume. Just released 4th quarter revenue and it’s as expected. Up 21%, all yearly revenue up. Payed off some of their long term debt and got an upgraded by Moody’s last week. Compared to Michael’s stock, their biggest competitor ,at $22 . 2020 saw a surge in home made, Etsy, clothing makers and is expected to remain steady.
